\par
Avorion always merges faces.\par
\par
3.2 Greedy Meshing Rules\par
\par
\f3\u10004?\f1  \f0 Only merge faces with:\par
\par
Same material\par
\par
Same orientation\par
\par
Same shape face\par
\par
\f3\u10004?\f1  \f0 Never merge across block types\par
\par
3.3 Chunk Strategy (Recommended)\par
Ship\par
\f1  \f3\u9500?\u9472?\f1  \f0 Chunk (16\'d716\'d716)\par
\f1  \f3\u9474?\f1    \f3\u9500?\u9472?\f1  \f0 Material A mesh\par
\f1  \f3\u9474?\f1    \f3\u9500?\u9472?\f1  \f0 Material B mesh\par
\par
\par
Rebuild only affected chunks on edit or damage.\par
\par
3.4 Greedy Face Merge (Concept)\par
for each axis\par
    for each slice\par
        find rectangles of identical faces\par
        emit one quad instead of many\par
\par
